# Chapter 4 - AI Meets Astrophysics: Black Hole Data Analysis

This project demonstrates using Machine Learning to predict black hole mass based on X-ray emission data.

## Features

- Synthetic dataset simulating black hole X-ray features.
- Linear regression model to predict mass.
- Performance evaluation with MSE and RÂ² metrics.
- Visualization of actual vs predicted values.

## Requirements

- Python 3.x  
- pandas  
- scikit-learn  
- matplotlib  

## How to Run

1. Clone the repo.  
2. Run the notebook in Google Colab or locally.  
3. Analyze model results and visualization.

## References

- [Machine Learning in Astrophysics Review](https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.07368)  
- [NASA HEASARC Data Archive](https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov)  
- [Scikit-learn Documentation](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/)
